The Wellsboro Area School District is currently accepting applications for the following openings:

High School Social Studies Teacher
Elementary Teacher

A complete application portfolio is required before interview and includes: letter of interest, resume, state standard teaching application form, appropriate PA teaching certificate, original transcripts, three current letters of reference and current Act 34, 114 and 151 clearances. Candidates may apply to Linda Gamble, Secretary to the Superintendent, Wellsboro Area School District, 227 Nichols Street, Wellsboro, PA 16901. Will not accept faxed applications. Visit www.wellsborosd.org for application and clearance forms. For additional information, please call (570) 724-0303 or email lgamble@wellsborosd.org. OPEN UNTIL FILLED. The Wellsboro Area School District is an EOE in compliance with Title IX, Title VI and Section 504.

post_text:
If you are wondering how the new guidance provided yesterday by the PA Dept of Education impacts schools across the state, this article provides some clarity. The WASD is currently working to develop a plan using this guidance and new guidance anticipated to be released in the next two weeks.

Under the state’s plan, schools can begin reopening after July 1, but before they reopen, the local school board must approve a health and safety plan spelling out its plan for social-distancing at school and that plan must be presented to the Department of Education.

We will continue to provide information and will be asking for input from our community as we develop our plan.

Thank you for your patience and understanding as we navigate these unknowns and new guidance.

https://www.dailyitem.com/news/state-provides-guidelines-for-schools-to-reopen/article_70f3522d-4b41-5819-857a-860503e61dc6.html

Attention Wellsboro High School Students:

Beginning tomorrow, Tuesday June the 2nd until Friday June the 5th, student items may be dropped at the front office of the High School from 8am- 3pm.

Items should be placed in the appropriate labeled boxes on the tables in front of the school.

This will ensure that you do not have to enter the building.

The following items should be returned:
- Laptops
- Textbooks
- library books
- parking passes and
- locker keys

All items should be turned in by Friday, June 5th at 3:00.
Please do not turn in your books and laptops until you have finished all your academic requirements.
If you have any questions please call the school at 570-724-3547.

To any parents who may have missed the survey that was sent: the Wellsboro Area School District will be providing free grab and go lunches for any school district students from noon to 2pm beginning Monday. Lunches may be picked up at the Wellsboro Fire Hall Annex, 21 East Avenue in Wellsboro. Students will be offered two days’ worth of lunches each visit. Lunches will be available for pick up this week Monday through Friday and the week of March 23rd on Monday, Wednesday and Friday. Additional days will be added based on need. Students do not need their lunch number to participate.

Students do not need to be with the parents when the lunches are picked up and friends, neighbors, and family are welcome to pick up lunches with a note from the parent.

Edit: We added the clarification that students can get two days of lunches each time they come. We did not mean they can only get two lunches over the two weeks.

post_text:
Beginning Friday, March 13th, Governor Wolf has asked that all communities not hold any public events larger than 250 people. Therefore, to honor this request, we must limit our attendance at all events, including this weekend’s high school musical production of South Pacific. To allow for a larger audience at the Saturday evening performance, we will be cancelling the Saturday matinee. Sorry for the inconvenience this may cause, however we will be monitoring our ticket sales very closely. Thank you for your continued support. This does not affect tonight’s performance.

To clarify the Saturday performances, we're cancelling the matinee to allow for a "full" audience of approximately 200 at the evening performance because they would count as one event.

We have just started the 2019 edition of our pig project! If you remembered our very successful project with Mabel two years ago – we will be conducting the project in a similar way.

Wellsboro High School Agriscience classes will be studying the reproduction of a pig over the next few weeks. A 1 year old Hampshire cross gilt named Daisy arrived in our classroom this week. She is almost at full term in her gestation and will give birth here. We will study the piglets for the first few weeks before they go back to the farm. You can join along monitoring the progress of Daisy and the piglets on our Daisy Cam link found here: http://vc.iu17.org/videos/livestreams/page1/

If you have questions about Daisy or the process, you can send them in on our program twitter account: @WellsboroAg or by emailing Mrs. Berndtson at mberndtson@wellsborosd.org.

A message about today's lockdown at Wellsboro High School:

At 9:35 this morning, the HS ran a routine lock down drill. All went smoothly.

At 10:40 the alarm system was reactivated. We treated this alert as an actual event because it was NOT initiated by administration. Local law enforcement responded as per protocol. The building was searched by law enforcement and determined to be safe. Students resumed normal activity at 11:55.

The district and law enforcement are working together to be sure that this does not happen again.

Student safety is our priority.

Wellsboro Area School District will be placing unused and unnecessary items for bid on www.municibid.com. The bids will open on Monday, July 30, 2018 and close on Thursday, August 9, 2018. To access the items,click here: https://www.municibid.com/Browse/R3777835/Pennsylvania?Seller=WellsboroAreaSD or visit www.municibid.com, select Pennsylvania then scroll to access the different items for bid from Wellsboro Area School District. Bids can only be placed through www.municibid.com. Items will not be for bid at Wellsboro Area School District. A list of items to be listed on the bid site can be found on the district’s website (www.wellsborosd.org).

If you have any questions please contact Brian Kennedy at 570-724-0308 or bkennedy@wellsborosd.org.

Wellsboro Parks & Recreation has a limited quantity of reduced price tickets to regional theme parks/attractions. You do not have to be a WASD resident, however the tickets must be purchased in person at the Parks & Rec Office (WASD Admin Building), 227 Nichols St, Wellsboro PA.

Save some money on these awesome destinations:
Knoebels Amusement Park
Baltimore Aquarium
Adventure Aquarium (Camden, NJ)
Maryland Zoo (Baltimore, MD)
Philadelphia Zoo
Dorney Park (Allentown, PA)
Franklin Institute (Philadelphia, PA)
PA Renaissance Festival (Lancaster, PA)
Hesheypark (Hershey, PA)
Pittsburgh Zoo
Crayola Experience (Easton, PA)
Six Flags Great Adventure (Jackson, NJ)

Tickets are available for purchase now!
